571:the same report noise report = v + Normal(0, τ); each arm acts on its **own noisy
572:estimate** and is eligible to fund a project only where *its own* estimated net is
573:positive (no oracle gate). They differ in exactly one way — the coverage
574:mechanism. *Distributed (endogenous coverage):* each interested citizen reports
575:independently with probability p if her value v ≥ 0 and p·(1 − β) if v < 0 (adverse
576:voice bias), giving ĥS_D = Σreports / p, ranked by estimated net per cost.
577:*Central (competent value-reader):* an appraisal budget equal to the distributed
578:arm's *expected* total reports in that world, spread **evenly** across projects
579:(fixed bandwidth); it samples interested citizens, observes v + Normal(0, τ), and
580:ranks by score = (1 − λ)·z(net/cost) + λ·z(P/cost), where P is claimable political
581:credit — the electoral credit-claiming and traceability logic by which visible,
582:attributable benefits are favoured over diffuse ones (Mayhew 1974; Arnold 1990) —
583:and λ is bounded credit pressure (a *posited* pressure whose real-world magnitude
584:must be measured, not assumed). Credit moves *ranking*, never eligibility (no
585:knowingly value-destroying planner). Delivered value is scored on
586:true net over each arm's funded set; the estimand is **Δ = (D − C)/O** per world,
587:where O is a full-information greedy benchmark (a reference level, not an optimum).
588:The frozen grid sweeps λ ∈ {0, 0.1, 0.2, 0.3} (λ = 0 a negative control), realized
589:corr(S, P) ∈ {0, 0.5, 1}, and h ∈ {1.5, 2.5, 4} over 100 seeded worlds, in a
590:baseline observation regime (p = .35, β = .30, τ = .5) and a matched-budget
591:low-information stress regime (p = .15, β = .60, τ = 1.0). The **pre-registered
592:decision rule** — frozen before running and designed by the independent auditor to
593:be adversarial — required, for a GO on rebuilding the quantitative engine, at least
594:15 of the 18 primary cells with mean Δ > 0, a pooled **median Δ ≥ 0.05**, a
595:bootstrap lower bound > 0, and median Δ ≥ 0 under the stress regime. The result was
596:**NO-GO**: the advantage was positive in all 18 primary cells, but the
597:pre-registered pooled **median Δ = 0.025**, below the 0.05 rebuild gate; the
598:negative control (λ = 0) sat at ≈ 0.016, indicating no hidden asymmetry favouring
599:the distributed arm. A **post-hoc** world-cluster ratio-of-sums estimate was
600:Δ = 0.026 [0.023, 0.029] (Monte-Carlo uncertainty on the simulated
601:data-generating process, reported separately from the median). The advantage rises
602:with credit pressure λ and falls as credit aligns with value — the
603:credit-versus-coverage mechanism — but it is small, which is why the calibrated
604:multiplier is retired and the paper rests on the architecture and the mechanism
605:direction.
