1013:audit parameters, are *consistent with* the documented range — this parameterizes
1014:the baseline's leak, it does not calibrate the institutional treatment effect. And the bias
1015:sweep bounds the open-construction claim honestly: distributed
1016:selection degrades near-linearly with coordinated signal capture and
1017:crosses below a competent full-coverage municipal planner only at
1018:roughly a thirty percent coordinated share — it degrades, never
1019:collapses, and remains superior everywhere below ten percent.
1020:
1021:A pre-registered eighth experiment (E8,
1022:`research/e8-behavioral-participation-design.md`) then replaced the
1023:participation side of these arms — the default share and informed share
1024:the architecture arms had imposed — with adoption trajectories generated
1025:by a companion behavioral study: a Core v0-conformant agent-based model
1026:of awareness, registration, participation modes, and trusted
1027:microdelegation, calibrated with LLM-elicited synthetic priors
1028:(replication package: the distributed-governance-experiments
1029:repository). The earlier apparatus produced 2.26 [2.23, 2.30] at scale under its
1030:synthetic adoption assumptions and 2.15–2.9× across three populations and all
1031:scales, including a launch trajectory that begins near zero
1032:participation — which costs 1.7% of the ratio, because the default layer
1033:anchors the thin early cycles by construction. The behavioral study also
1034:independently reproduces the informed-share assumption these experiments
1035:had imposed: 0.309 emergent against the 0.30 assumed.
1036:
1037:**What survives.** Stripped to what the governing test supports: (1) under the
1038:pre-registered symmetric gate the distributed selection advantage is *positive but
1039:small* (median Δ = 0.025, below the 0.05 rebuild gate; NO-GO); (2) the load-bearing
1040:contributions are the architecture and the qualitative credit-versus-coverage
1041:mechanism — credit-pressured central ranking underweights diffuse value that
1042:coverage-based distributed selection surfaces; (3) every compound ratio above
1043:(2.19×/2.22×/2.26×, +43%, +53–54%, ~2×–5×) is a conditional, model-internal
1044:apparatus output, not a calibrated effect; and (4) any calibrated total delivered-
1045:value effect — selection *and* delivery, on real data — remains future work.

### drafts/paper.md:1348
1348:distributional and rights constraints this model does not represent. This
1349:paper's contribution is an architecture that makes that criterion
1350:operational — and a disciplined account of exactly how far its evidence
1351:reaches. The
1352:architecture's spine is two separable questions anyone can ask. First:
1353:take the same projects, designed identically, and change only who
1354:executes and how they are watched — does the visibly audited regime with
1355:reputational consequences deliver more than the one without them? Second:
1356:hold the control layer fixed and change only which projects get funded,
1357:centrally planned or socially prioritized? In the exploratory simulation
1358:apparatus the answer to both is yes — a verified-delivery gain and a
1359:selection gain that interact rather than merely add — but those
1360:magnitudes are model-internal factorial contrasts, not calibrated
1361:effects, and we do not build the paper on them. The claim the paper
1362:actually stands on is narrower and was tested harder: a pre-registered,
1363:symmetric, selection-only gate finds the distributed-minus-central
1364:advantage positive in every cell but small (a pre-registered pooled median
1365:Δ = 0.025 of a full-information benchmark, below its pre-set 0.05
1366:research-program rebuild gate), so we retire the compound multiplier an
1367:earlier version reported and rest on the architecture and the *direction*
1368:of the mechanism. One model-internal result is worth carrying because it is
1369:about the delivery layer, not the multiplier: in the model, at the
1370:audit-documented detection intensity, detection without persistent
1371:consequences deters no diversion; what moves delivered value is the
1372:instrument the modelled status quo lacks — consequences that persist. Whether
1373:that holds in a real institution is a hypothesis for a pilot, not a result
1374:here; but the model is unambiguous that accountability without memory is
1375:bookkeeping.
1376:
1377:The deeper point is Friedman's: a central administration spends other
1378:people's money on other people, the spending category with the least care
1379:for both cost and value (Friedman and Friedman 1980). This architecture
1380:does not answer that problem with exhortation; it re-plumbs the bucket.

