759:## How this model has been tested so far
760:
761:This document's claims do not rest on enthusiasm. The underlying corpus
762:was stress-tested three ways before publication (adversarially, formally,
763:and computationally); the computational part is a **stylized model**, not a
764:validated implementation, and its magnitudes are conditional (see the
765:correction banner above):
766:
767:- **Adversarially.** Forty-three attack briefs grounded in the political
768:  science and economics literature — from metric gaming and fiscalizer
769:  capture to clientelism, polarization, and fiscal strangulation — each
770:  answered by a paired defense and an accepted resolution under an
771:  explicit integrate-or-bound rule; none was dismissed, several are
772:  honestly answered "bounded, not solved" (`attacks/`, `defenses/`,
773:  resolutions `docs/67`–`docs/113`, rule `knowledge/principles/P007`).
774:- **Formally.** The disbursement and anti-collusion mechanisms are proven
775:  as incentive-compatibility and collusion-proofness conditions, with the
776:  design levers appearing as explicit terms (the formal companion note).
777:- **Computationally.** A 10,000-agent simulation of realistic citizen
778:  attention found that funding caps curb concentration but not quality,
779:  that allocation quality is carried by the informational quality of the
780:  project prioritization the passive share follows (the aggregated
781:  allocation profiles), and that — in the tested 24-cycle grid, as active
782:  evaluation fell from 10% to 2% — a strong default anchor buffered the
783:  *aggregate* selection loss, though within-cycle alignment still eroded in
784:  every condition (a conditional model result, not evidence of deployment
785:  resilience; the matched-budget symmetry gate couples both arms' information
786:  to participation and cannot establish participation-decay resilience). A pre-registered fourth
787:  experiment modeled knowledge symmetrically and found that building the
788:  weight vector from aggregated dispersed citizen signals tracks value more
789:  closely than fixed-bandwidth central construction — provided an
790:  aggregation institution exists and signals are honest. Earlier
791:  agent-based experiments (E5/E7/E8) reported a compound value-per-budget
792:  **multiplier (~2×); that multiplier is now RETIRED as a calibrated
793:  effect.** A later, pre-registered **symmetric, selection-only stress
794:  test** — both arms with matched expected appraisal budgets, delivery at
795:  parity, each acting on its own noisy estimate rather than ground truth —
796:  returned **NO-GO**: the distributed-minus-central selection advantage is
797:  **positive in every pre-specified cell but small (pre-registered pooled
798:  median Δ = 0.025 of a full-information benchmark, below its pre-set 0.05
799:  research-program rebuild gate; a post-hoc ratio-of-sums estimate was
800:  Δ = 0.026 [0.023, 0.029])**. So the
801:  honest computational finding is a **directional** one — credit-pressured
802:  central selection mis-allocates relative to coverage-based distributed
803:  selection — not a headline multiplier; the earlier figures survive only
804:  as conditional outputs of that earlier apparatus. The sixth experiment
805:  (E6) isolated the incentive channel with an all-honest executor pool and
806:  found that visible reputational competition sustains executor effort
807:  where opacity lets it collapse, while warning that naive
808:  reputation-weighted assignment concentrates work faster than it finds
809:  ability. These results discipline this document's claims rather than
810:  decorate them; the controlling specification is

